practice.statement:
Let $(a, b, c)$ be a real solution of the system of equations
\begin{align*} x^3 - xyz &= 2 \\ y^3 - xyz &= 6 \\ z^3 - xyz &= 20 \end{align*}
The greatest possible value of $a^3 + b^3 + c^3$ can be written in the form $\frac{m}{n}$, where $m$ and $n$ are relatively prime positive integers. Find $m + n$.
